      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Java 9 is going to use a single byte per character for strings having only iso-latin-1 content, so such strings can have as many characters as the heap in bytes (or max array length, whatever is smaller), but on the other hand, since non-latin strings use two bytes in an array, the maximum string length will be halved for them in Java 9, only supporting 1073741823 characters."
