    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You should be able to get a String of length </p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p><a href=\"http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/docs/api/java/lang/Integer.html#MAX_VALUE\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>Integer.MAX_VALUE</code></a> always <strong>2,147,483,647</strong> (2<sup>31</sup> - 1)<br>\n(Defined by the Java specification, the maximum size of an array, which the String class uses for internal storage)<br>\nOR  </p></li>\n<li><p><code>Half your maximum heap size</code> (since each character is two bytes) <strong>whichever is smaller</strong>.</p></li>\n</ol>\n"
