      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
      "body" : "The problem is &quot;For each K, output the smallest palindrome larger than K.&quot; (where K is the number given). It would be trivially simple to output the first palindrome smaller than K. You require arithmetic to find one larger than K. Example: Find the next palindrome larger than 999999999999, or the next palindrome larger than 12922."
