      "body" : "@awksp: <code>char</code> is 16 bits, but a <i>character</i> in a <code>String</code> can occupy <i>two</i> <code>char</code>&#39;s (two &#39;surrogate&#39; code elements to represent one character in UTF16). However, the Q was only for <i>decimal digits</i> and these are not only BMP but 8859-1/block0 and ASCII."
