    "answer_id" : 43699751,
    "question_id" : 1179983,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Java9 uses byte[] to store String.value, so you can only get about 1GB Strings in Java9. Java8 on the other hand can have 2GB Strings.</p>\n\n<p>By character I mean \"char\"s, some character is not representable in BMP(like some of the emojis), so it will take more(currently 2) chars.</p>\n"
